               <nationality type="Ethiopia"/>
               <faith type="EOTC"/>
               <occupation type="political">prince</occupation>
               <birth when="1923">He was born in <placeName ref="LOC1216AddisA"/> in <date>1923</date>.</birth>

               <floruit notBefore="1941" notAfter="1957">He was the third child of <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS5226haylase"/> and
                  <roleName type="title">ʾǝtege</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS6642MananAs"/>. He received his education at St Christopher's school,
                  <placeName ref="wd:Q22889"/>, Wellington College and Gordonstoun, while staying with his father in exile during the Italian occupation.
                  After the liberation in <date>1941</date>, he was given the title <roleName type="title">masfǝna Ḥarar</roleName>
                  which made him the governor general of the large province of <placeName ref="LOC3787Hararg"/>. In <date>1944</date>,
                  he became governor of the town but spent most of the time at the Emperor's court in <placeName ref="LOC1216AddisA"/>.
                  In <date>1946</date>, he married <persName ref="PRS8527SaraGez"/> with whom he had five sons.
                  He was the favourite son of the Emperor and that his father preferred the succession to be passed to him rather than to his elder brother
                  <persName ref="PRS2112AsfaWas"/>. Respected as a good officer serving in the air force and an imaginative bussinessman. </floruit>

               <death when="1957">He died in <placeName ref="LOC1216AddisA"/> in <date>1957</date>.</death>

            </person>
